POLICE are probing the discovery of an injured man near a beach.
The 45-year-old man was found on Gypsy Brae, near Cramond Beach, in Edinburgh last night.
He was taken by ambulance to Edinburgh Royal Infirmary where his condition was described as “stable”.
Officers were called to the West Shore Road area at around 11pm following reports from the public who had concerns about the man.
Police are appealing to anyone who many have seen “anything suspicious” in the vicinity around that time.
But is understood the man’s injuries are likely to have been non-suspicious.
